The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 December is 17,305 (2,002.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 December, there were 3,015 new confirmed cases (349.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 December, there were 1,839 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 64% (1,176 extra cases).
